text:
For new fans: 
(in age order)

Scoups(Seungcheol): baggy jeans, grey button up over white shirt, yellowish beanie.

Jeonghan: All beige outfit, arm sling
Joshua: Black basketball shorts, white shirt, blue button up overtop
Jun(Junhui): Gren jeans with black side panels at bottom, dark grey tshirt with writing on it
Hoshi(Soonyoung): Camo pants, plaid button up shirt
Wonwoo: Beige pants, cream tshirt
Woozi(Jihoon): All black outfit, black shorts, black tshirt
DK(Dokyeom/Seokmin): Beige shorts, grey tshirt with the number '955' on front
Mingyu: All black outfit, black hoodie, black shorts, black glasses
The8(Minghao): Jeans, green button up shirt tucked in, pink hair
Seungkwan: Grey shirts, cream shirt with blue heart, blue hair
Vernon(Hansol): Black pants (jeans?), grey tshirt
Dino(Chan): Cream pants and shirt, grey zipup hoodie on top.

Scoups is the leader
Units are: 
Hiphop unit: Scoups, Wonwoo, Mingyu, Vernon
Performnce Unit: Hoshi,Jun, The8, Dino
Vocal Unit: Joshua, Jeonghan, Woozi, Dokyeom, Seungkwan

Enjoy!

They are such good & expressive dancers (look at Jeonghan, even with his hurt arm he is still dancing well), so watching them dance is mesmerising and calming for me. Like children with cartoons kind of stuff. No thoughts, head empty, just 13 guys dancing perfectly in sync.

author: @nytsirhc6835
text:
some cute moments I want to treasure forever and that made me tear up bc of how HAPPY THEY ALL LOOK, seeing them enjoy life is my greatest carat wish

0:08 Mingyu and Woozi wearing matching clothes
0:09 Jun's "I did nothing. I just got lucky" shirt being the opposite of Jun but also being hilarious
0:11 Scoups looking so giggly and cute in his beanie, absolutely beaming at Hoshi
0:33 all the handholding! Hoshi and Jeonghan, Myungho and Josh, Dino and Seungkwan
0:38 look at them on the side, 'nuff said

0:49 Seungkwan smiling at Vernon
0:54 Seungkwan bending over laughing b/c of Dino
0:56 Mingyu doing a little bouncy walk
0:59 DK, Vernon, and Mingyu
1:02 Seungkwan hitting Wonwoo a little too hard
1:15 Josh slaying
1:19 Just...just everyone, look at everyone, their smiles are so wide I can see them with 360p
1:20 Dino's OH OH OH
1:21 Scoups living his life
1:22 Seungkwan surprised at Woozi fondly judging him
1:23 Vernon and Mingyu NAILING THAT HIGH-FIVE, under the leg too! + DK and Myungho
1:34 MORE HANDHOLDING I'M GOING TO COMBUST
1:35 Mingyu swinging Vernon's hand and sending the two of them and DK into the wall
1:40 Hoshi being Hoshi
1:56 everyone's smiles progressively getting wider as they turn their heads looking at Jun and then Dino
2:13 Mingyu and Wonwoo matching pose with their glasses
2:15 Jun and Myungho PERFECTLY aligned at the elbows
2:28 Jeonghan all throughout this video, but also just DANCING ON POINT WITH A CAST, jumping is CLEAN
3:07 DK clinging to a tsundere Woozi
3:08 Wonwoo highfiving Dino
3:10 Seungkwan heart!
3:11 WONWOO'S FREAKING ADORABLE THUMBS UP

p.s. Vernon needs to stop distracting me with his fit. I watched this 15 times and he distracted me from the members EACH TIME REEE
p.p.s. more Jeonghan appreciation, may he recover fast
p.p.p.s. Wonwoo actually made me tear up the whole time bc I'm just so happy to see him doing better

text:
THIS CHOREO IS SUCH A BANGER R U KIDDING ME. i love how smooth and witty the transitions are to new formations. there is so so much going on that it can appear a bit messy at some parts but that's what makes the transitions so so impressive; it's how quick and fast paced it is for them to make the transition of the new formation AND still be able to be understandable to the audience's eyes

like how hoshi quickly fades away from the center role from his line at 0:32 to passing the attention to dk at 0:37 by letting the whole group do the same dance move thus the viewers bringing their eyes to view the formation as a whole now and noticing the center which is dk. we have our eyes so focused on hoshi we don't really get to comprehend what's happening in the bg but as soon as dk's line begins everything just becomes instantly clear in a flash. some wizard magic goin on. THIS PRINCIPLE APPLIES AGAIN TO JEONGHAN'S LINE  AT 1:33 .. we focus on him so much that the transition to woozi center that starts off a bit clunky (because of all the sprinting and skipping happening in the bg lolol) that it's so so cool  how it smoothly instantly becomes a clearer as soon as jh becomes a part of the whole at 1:37, passing the eye of the audience to woozi next.

OR HOW THE8 AT 1:28 ALBEIT AT THE SIDELINE OF THE PART QUICKLY COMES TO VIEW AS THE CENTER FOR HIS LINE  BECAUSE OF HOW QUICK THEY FORM THE FORMATION  OF THE DUO LINES WHILE STILL BEING ABLE TO LET THE AUDIENCE'S VIEW EASILY ADJUST AND COMPREHEND IT 

OR AT HOW VERNON AT 1:13 BREAKS THE 13 PERSON FORMATION AND QUICKLY (SOMEHOW) MELTS INTO JUST 5 PEOPLE. IT HAPPENS SO FAST BUT WE CAN STILL EASILY UNDERSTAND WHAT'S GOING ON ++ THE WAY HE PASSES THE CENTER TO SCOUPS!!! IT JUST INSTANTLY MELTS AWAY IT'S MAGICAL 

im geeking out so so much this was done so well . everything i say is practically incomprehensive but main takeaway is i love the choreo. i was in awe the whole damn time it's so so fun it's literally magic T_______T so so amazing

author: @ScarletCloud
text:
I've just noticed in this choreo video the beautiful, creative (and kinda meaningful?) transition in 2:08. 

Jun's singing in the middle, next is Dino so he moves forward to the center. Then, in just a few seconds, Mingyu, Wonu and Vernon reagroup with Coups. Meanwhile, JeongHan, Joshua and Kwan run to reagroup with Woozi and DK. Vocal unit and hip hop unit moves in spiral during Mingyu and Seungkwan parts, and the center is being fullfilled with the performance unit having their own moves.

Edit: after seeing it again, more than spiral, it remind me more of the typical representation of the day, where sun and moon are moving to the same direction, opposite positioned, and Earth is in the middle.

MAGIC. /chef kiss
